Home / Elk Creek, Nebraska Niobium Project
















                                                            Elk Creek, Nebraska Niobium Project                                                  


NioCorp acquired the Elk Creek project in South East Nebraska on May 4th 2010. The Elk Creek project is a former Molycorp project. Molycorp left in the early 1990's when they left all of their exploration projects to focus on their Mountain Pass project in California. Over the past few decades Niobium demand and prices have increased several fold, which is why NioCorp has taken up where Molycorp left off.  WIth the limited number of niobium producers (3) and the dominant market share of CBMM Niobium prices are very stable and averaging $42 in 2013.
Based on current forecasts Niobium demand is going to surpass the supply capacity from the 3 existing producers.  All 3 (CBMM, Anglo American and IAMGOLD's Niobec) of the current producers are expanding production as they enjoy healthy profit margins from their Niobium operations. Despite this increase in production from the three producers, the possibility of demand outstripping supply by the end of the decade remains, opening the doors for additional production to fulfill market needs.
NioCorp's Elk Creek Niobium deposit is the only primary Niobium deposit in the US, and is the highest-grade, large-tonnage undeveloped deposit in North America.
Elk Creek Highlights:
NI 43-101 Resource Report Published in 2012 by Tetra Tech



